1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
A primitive action must change a meaningful contact state.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Face contact represents what motion is constrained.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Kuhn-Tucker constraints separate possible states from impossible ones.

4
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Seven contact classes create forty-nine candidate transitions.

5
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Physics reduces the graph to twenty executable transitions.

6
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Observed tasks concentrate on a smaller frequent subset.

7
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Physical manipulation agents are named edges in the filtered graph.

8
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:29,000
The next layer asks whether a physical edge makes semantic sense.
